      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ONE STUNIN MELODY (7) disappointed backers last time out when eighth, beaten 21 metres, over 1720m at Young. Form prior to that was far better, including a sound second over 1770m at Canberra two starts ago. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. Meets a similar line up and she is capable of a much better performance. SHOOBEES SUNSET (8) was prominent from the outset last time out and finished runner-up, beaten 1.75 metres, in a far better performance at Young over 1720m. Primary contender in a similar assignment. BARKWAY THOMAS (9) is the best of the rest after finishing fifth over 1720m at Young last time out. Tricky draw for EMIKO (10) but there was merit in the latest effort.",
